data.subject: ComfyUI-bleh BlehInsaneChainSampler
data.question: What node was added on 20240208 in ComfyUI-bleh that could impact TAESD decoding performance?
data.answer: On 20240208, the BlehInsaneChainSampler node was added in ComfyUI-bleh. It allows running previews on a specific device and skipping TAESD upscale layers for increased TAESD decoding performance.

data.subject: ComfyUI-bleh BlehDeepShrink
data.question: What new node was added on 20240201 in ComfyUI-bleh, and what new features were added to it?
data.answer: The BlehDeepShrink node was added on 20240201 in ComfyUI-bleh. New features include additional upscale/downscale methods and the ability to set a higher downscale factor and enable antialiasing for certain modes.

data.subject: ComfyUI-bleh TAESD previewer
data.question: What changes were made to the TAESD previewer in ComfyUI-bleh on 20240128?
data.answer: The TAESD previewer had its CUDA-specific stuff removed as the performance gains were marginal but it majorly affected VRAM usage. Heuristics for batch preview layout were hopefully improved, and a `maxed_batch_step_mode` setting was added. The fixed reversed HyperTile default start/end step values, and it was allowed to only apply HyperTile at a step interval.
